examples.en: What are you staring at?
It's rude to stare.
She gave him a cold stare.
Ann stared before her.
She stared out the window.
She gave him a long look / stare.
He gave me a frosty stare.
His mother told him not to stare.
The students stared at the teacher with amazement.
She stared at me in disbelief.
Children enjoy a silly competition in which they try to stare each other down.
They looked at me with accusing stares.
He treated me to a cold, unblinking stare.
She gave him a long hard stare.
He can hypnotize people with his stare.
She gave him a stony stare.
Duvall gave him a flinty stare.
He gave her a penetrating stare.
She sat there staring into space (=looking for a long time at nothing).
She squirmed under her father's angry stare.
I tried to avoid his piercing stare.
His glassy stare made my flesh creep.
Rachel fixed him with an icy stare.
He was gazing out the window with a glassy stare.
Carr wouldn't meet Feng's stare, which was openly hostile.
She laughed, ignoring the stares of everyone around her.
There was a silence as the women turned with one accord to stare at Doreen.
